txt.en: You have defeated Bittergall and her children, and freed the lands of North Ithilien from her grasp.\n\nThe Rangers spoke in whispers of a great spider in the hills of the Ephel Dúath, and perhaps you have done what they feared impossible.

Bittergall can be found to the west of Bâr Aroth wandering under the shadows of the trees of North Ithilien.\n\nYou have encountered Bittergall and her children and should defeat them before your adventures take you beyond North Ithilien.
You have defeated Bittergall and her children, and freed the lands of North Ithilien from her grasp.

Skittering down from the Ephel Dúath, a fell creature has taken refuge under the thick trees of North Ithilien.

Named Bittergall by the Rangers, this massive spider stalks the lands of Ithilien in search of new prey and a new home to grow her brood.

You should defeat Bittergall before her children can overrun North Ithilien.
Terrible are the great spiders of Middle-earth, and worse still are those that stray from the caverns of the Ephel Dúath.
You have defeated Bittergall and her brood!
